y of Novo Nordisk goes back 90 years. It began when August Krogh, a Nobel Prize-winning professor at the University of Copenhagen, decided he wanted to start producing a revolutionary new medical preparation called insulin.       Novo Nordisk History                                    This page is intended for members of the UK public  UK/WB/1215/0033(7) March 2018                           Novo Nordisk 2016/17 Gender Pay Report  Read more     Novo Nordisk Tax Strategy  Read More                  Accessibility        Who we are  Novo Nordisk is a global healthcare company with more than 90 years of innovation and leadership in diabetes care. This heritage has given us experience and capabilities that also enable us to help people defeat other serious chronic conditions: haemophilia, growth disorders and obesity.  Headquartered in Denmark, Novo Nordisk employs approximately 42,100 people  in 79 countries, and markets its products in more than 170 countries.       Other NN websites  novonordiskfoundation.co.uk  An independent charitable organisation supporting diabetes research.           changingdiabetesresearch.co.uk   Novo Nordisk Volunteer Outreach Programme - putting researchers in touch with people who are interested in taking part in research.     novonordisk-trials.com  This website contains information about all Novo Nordisk sponsored clinical trials.                      ® 2018 Novo Nordisk Ltd  Disclaimer / Cookie policy                         